A map for css

My first ever zombie mod map.  It's like a bonus map for my wintermaze_2016 series.
When I made Wintermaze_2016_V5 I thought to myself "It would make a decent zm map. 
So I made a few modifications and here you go! 

And yes the helicopter and trains are functional. No, it wont be impossible to escape zombies, for you can walk on the cables and helicopter cannot be stopped mid air, and you need time to get it in the air. 

Now what are some of the differences between this and the aim version of this map? 
  • Helicopter cannot be stopped mid air (I removed the "STOP" button).
  • You can walk on ALL the cables, including the train ones. 
  • Some containers have boxes in em. 
  • The "security room" has a tunnel near ceiling which leads into the prototype room, allowing players to gain high ground. But it's not as easy as it looks to get there. 
This is my first ever ZM map. I hope it works well... IF not, if you have any ideas/suggestions, please let me know! 

The inspiration for this map came from cs_alpin. A good old map that is dear to my hart and was a favorite during the good ol' 1.6 days. 
That map could be played as both a cs and zm map, which is why I thought that with a little bit modification this map could also work in a similar fasion...
Thanks for playing

Zombie_City is a map created by Valve (or possibly Turtle Rock Studios) that was a part of the map sources folder that released today. It is likely the starting point of Left 4 Dead, and for those of you who have heard the name "Terror-Strike" before, you will love to get the chance to play this prototype level.

My upload fixes a texture by adding a new material for it. I have also created an overview texture, generated a nav mesh, and added a level description, all of which are conveniently packed into the bsp itself for maximum convenience. Try it out and let me know how you think!

CS:GO VERSION
THIS IS A PORT OF A CSGO MAP I DID NOT CREATE THIS!



A map for the MAPEADORES ZOMBIE APOCALYPSE Mapping Contest!

Uptop an ancient mountain lies a Sanctuary of hope. Due to unforseen consequences, the holy land has been infected by a sinister plague.
Triggering the altar within the Sanctuary should be sufficient to wipe out the plague.

The map features:
-A beautiful marble castle to shoot zombies (or chop humans into bits!)
-Varied difficulty defense points
-Engaging zombie teleports to keep them in the action
-Souls-genre ambient music, matching the vibe of the map
-No bullshit, items, lasers or bosses. Just classic ZE gameplay!

Spent a couple weeks making this with some off days. Very quickly made so I could release it on christmas, but I did put a lot of time in even if it might not show.

Please message me if you find any bugs, gameplay or otherwise.

Edit: Forgot to include the triggers on compile yesterday so redownload it. :)
